Use i and j to denote even and odd indices, respectively.
Loop through input array,
1. locate next wrongly placed item with odd index j;
2. if current even-index item, A[i], is wrongly placed, swap it with A[j]; otherwise, forward to the next even index;

Time: O(n), space: O(1).

```
    public int[] sortArrayByParityII(int[] A) {
        for (int i = 0, j = 1; i < A.length; i += 2) {
            while (j < A.length && A[j] % 2 == 1) { j += 2; } //find next odd-index item A[j] with even value.
            if (A[i] % 2 == 1) { // if odd-index item A[i] is odd, swap it with A[j].
                int t = A[i];
                A[i] = A[j];
                A[j] = t;
                j += 2;
            }
        }
        return A;
    }
```

