Even & odd indices 
1) maintain two indices "even" and "odd" which start at 0 and 1 spectively;
2) loop through elements in array;
3) if element is of odd parity, copy it to position of "odd" index and increase odd by two; if element is of even parity, copy it to positon of "even" index and increase even by two.
```
class Solution:
    def sortArrayByParityII(self, A: List[int]) -> List[int]:
        ans = [None] * len(A)
        index = [0, 1] #even & odd indices
        for x in A:
            ans[index[x%2]] = x
            index[x%2] += 2
        return ans 
```

